9. Findings

Finding 1

OpenAI and Anthropic are not secret state laboratories. They are civilian institutions operating in public life and commercial markets.

Finding 2

A Public Benefit Corporation is not a republic.

Finding 3

A nonprofit foundation is not an electorate.

Finding 4

A safety committee is not consent.

Finding 5

Closed models are not automatically safer. They are automatically less inspectable.

Finding 6

Open models are not automatically safe. They are automatically less monopolized.

Finding 7

If AI is too dangerous for the public, it is too dangerous for private executives.

Finding 8

If AI is safe enough for private executives, the public is entitled to ask why it is uniquely unsafe in everyone else’s hands.

Finding 9

Dario Amodei, while technically correct that open-weight AI is not identical to traditional open-source software, is acting as a knobhead when he treats that distinction as though it settles the question of who deserves power.

