10. Policy Recommendations

10.1 Symmetric Safety Standards

Any safety standard applied to open models must also apply to closed labs. The public should reject one-way rules that burden open development while allowing closed frontier labs to continue scaling under private discretion.

10.2 Public Accountability Before Public Restriction

No restriction on civilian model development should be justified by private-lab testimony alone. If the public is to be limited, the evidence must be public, reviewable, contestable, and independent.

10.3 No Moral Monopoly by Branding

Terms such as “responsible,” “benefit,” “alignment,” “safety,” and “humanity” must not be treated as magic words that convert private power into democratic legitimacy.

10.4 The Dave Rule

Any proposed AI regulation must answer the following:

Why is Dave in Accounting categorically less entitled to build or modify AI than an unelected CEO?

If the answer is “compute,” regulate compute.
If the answer is “capability,” regulate capability.
If the answer is “risk,” regulate risk.
If the answer is “because Dave is not us,” reject the proposal.

